Breakfast and lunch are free to all students until December 31, 2020.

A la carte snacks and drinks will be available for purchase starting Monday. We are requesting that you load money onto your student's account via MySchoolBucks in order to facilitate a true touchless meal. However cash will still be accepted. Visit the Food Service page on the district site, www.wcsd.org, for a link to MySchoolBucks.

post_text:
The District would like to take a moment and thank our exceptional maintenance staff. This team does an amazing job under normal circumstances, but since March, they have stepped up and done an outstanding job. They have disinfected, cleaned, waxed, mowed, moved furniture and done it all over again the next day. They have made our buildings and grounds safe and clean for our students and staff and they are prepared for all new procedures they have been tasked with when students return next week.

We are very fortunate to have such a dedicated and hardworking maintenance team!

As we move towards the start of the new school year, we are continuing to develop our reopening plan that meets the guidelines set by NYSDOH, NYSED and the CDC. Yesterday, a letter with an overview of our reopening plan, was mailed to every household with students in the district. Included in that letter is instructions on how to notify the district if you plan to keep your child(ren) home. The letter and reopening plan overview are also posted on our website along with the complete reopening plan, FAQ and Learning Preference Form. As always, if you have any questions, please email reopeningwcsd@wcsd.org or call (518)623-2861.

post_text:
Dear Students and Families,
Beginning Monday, June 15 th and continuing to June 17 th , (see schedule below) we will have
three “exchange days” to return items that belong to school, to give students the items from their
hall locker and give students an opportunity to go into the locker rooms and get their athletic
equipment. Our staff will be here to see you and collect the items to be returned.
Stations will be set up in along the driveway used for the busses in front of the building to return
the following items:
 Chromebooks
 Textbooks
 Band instruments
 Band Uniforms
 Calculators
 Athletic uniforms and practice gear
 Library Books
 Art Supplies
 Guitars
So we can do this in an organized and orderly fashion please adhere to the following
schedule
 Monday, June 15, 2pm-5pm – 7 th and 8 th Grade
 Tuesday, June 16, 2pm-5pm – 9 th and 10 th Grade
 Wednesday, June 17, 2pm-5pm – 11 th and 12 th Grade
If you have any questions, please call 518-623-2861 extension 222.

Thank you and we look forward to seeing you!

Mr. Duell

Dear Students and Families,
Beginning Monday, June 15 th and continuing to June 17 th , (see schedule below) we will have
three “exchange days” to return items that belong to school, to give students the items from their
hall locker and give students an opportunity to go into the locker rooms and get their athletic
equipment. Our staff will be here to see you and collect the items to be returned.
Stations will be set up in along the driveway used for the busses in front of the building to return
the following items:
 Chromebooks
 Textbooks
 Band instruments
 Band Uniforms
 Calculators
 Athletic uniforms and practice gear
 Library Books
 Art Supplies
 Guitars
So we can do this in an organized and orderly fashion please adhere to the following
schedule
 Monday, June 15, 2pm-5pm – 7 th and 8 th Grade
 Tuesday, June 16, 2pm-5pm – 9 th and 10 th Grade
 Wednesday, June 17, 2pm-5pm – 11 th and 12 th Grade
If you have any questions, please call 518-623-2861 extension 222.

Thank you and we look forward to seeing you!

Mr. Duell

post_text: On Memorial Day, 8th grade student Caden signaled "Taps" at the War Memorial in Warrensburg, in participating in the "Taps Across America" event. This movement invited veterans, musicians, teachers, and students of all abilities and ages to sound "Taps" on their front lawns, porches, and driveways at 3 p.m. local time on Monday, May 25. Fun fact - "Taps" is a bugle signal, not a song. Take a listen to his first ever time performing it. Fanstastic performance Caden!

Warrensburg CSD libraries would like to remind students about the ebook/audiobook lending library called Sora, provided to us through WSWHE BOCES. Students can borrow ebooks and audiobooks for two weeks at a time and can download them onto any device.

To log in, click https://soraapp.com/welcome. Click on the green box that says “My School is a WSWHE Library BOCES System.” If this doesn't pop up, you might have to type in "WSWHE Boces." Next, use the dropdown menu to find Warrensburg Central School District. Then, click “Sign in Using Warrensburg Central School District.” Your login is your school email address and your regular classroom password. Email casabonnej@wcsd.org for more information. Borrow an ebook or audiobook to read and listen to today!

SUNY is excited to announce their first ever virtual college fairs on Thursday, May 14 from 3p-7p and Saturday, May 16 from 1p-6p! The fair will include representatives from nearly every SUNY campus. During the fair students will be able to communicate with campus representatives using text and video chat.

This is a unique opportunity to explore all of the opportunities at The State University of New York: challenging academics; innovative research; global study; and financial support.

We hope your juniors and their families will attend. Please register at https://www.suny.edu/attend/events/virtual-college-fair/?fbclid=IwAR3X1EvaKXKd2-5ktdj_h5m1o6_M-bJeQviiECqrvuqyXyMYtCvE3w8oh3U

post_text: Spring is a great time to get outdoors, and regular exercise is an important part of a healthy lifestyle. Warren County is joining with the state Department of Environmental Conservation in asking that those who are venturing out onto the trails or into the woods to do so safely to avoid potential spread of COVID-19 at trailheads and mountain summits. We are asking for a #TrailsPledgeWarrenCounty to be safe and smart outdoors during this ongoing outbreak. Educational signs are going up at trailheads around the county. Click the link to learn more: https://www.dec.ny.gov/outdoor/7865.html

We have been hard at work both yesterday and this morning, preparing to hand out instructional materials. Please be patient as we will be working as quickly as we can to hand the materials out and follow the recommendations of the CDC and NYS Department of Health. We will only allow 10 people in each building at a time. While waiting, please remember to practice social distancing and keep 6 feet between you and the family in front of you. Thank you for your patience and understanding.
